<refnamediv>
<refname>gtpstatistics</refname>
<refpurpose>
Runs GTP commands on all positions of game collections.
</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
<cmdsynopsis>
<command>gtpstatistics</command>
<arg><option>-config</option> <replaceable>file</replaceable></arg>
<arg><option>-commands</option> <replaceable>commands</replaceable></arg>
<arg><option>-program</option> <replaceable>program</replaceable></arg>
<arg><option>-size</option> <replaceable>n</replaceable></arg>
<arg><option>-verbose</option></arg>
<arg choice="plain" rep="repeat">
<replaceable>file.sgf</replaceable>
</arg>
</cmdsynopsis>
<cmdsynopsis>
<command>gtpstatistics</command> <arg><option>-help</option></arg>
</cmdsynopsis>
<cmdsynopsis>
<command>gtpstatistics</command> <arg><option>-version</option></arg>
</cmdsynopsis>
<cmdsynopsis>
<command>gtpstatistics</command>
<arg><option>-analyze</option> <replaceable>file</replaceable></arg>
<arg><option>-config</option> <replaceable>file</replaceable></arg>
<arg><option>-force</option></arg>
<arg><option>-precision</option> <replaceable>n</replaceable></arg>
</cmdsynopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
<title>Description</title>
<para>
Runs a a set of commands for a Go program supporting the Go Text Protocol
on each position of Go game collections.
The results are stored in the text file "gtpstatistics.dat" in table format.
If gtpstatistics is run with the option <option>-analyze</option>, a HTML
file is produced, which contains summary statistics for this file.
</para>
<para>
Games must not contain setup stones.
On positions containing a move, the command <command>reg_genmove</command>
is run first for the color of the move, and the generated move is compared to
the actual move. This result is stored in the table, too.
</para>
<para>
The return value of <command>gtpstatistics</command> is 0, if the run
completed successfully, -1 otherwise.
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
<title>Options</title>
<variablelist>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<option>-analyze</option> <replaceable>file</replaceable>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Analyze the result file
<filename><replaceable>file.dat</replaceable></filename>.
Creates a HTML file <filename><replaceable>file.html</replaceable></filename>
with summary statistics.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<option>-config</option> <replaceable>file</replaceable>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Read command line options and arguments from file.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<option>-commands</option> <replaceable>commands</replaceable>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Comma separated list of GTP commands to run on each position.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<option>-force</option>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Overwrite existing HTML file generated with option <option>-analyze</option>.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<option>-help</option>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Display help and exit.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<option>-precision</option> <replaceable>n</replaceable>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Maximum number of fraction digits for floating point numbers in output file.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<option>-program</option> <replaceable>command</replaceable>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Command line for running Go program.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<option>-size</option> <replaceable>n</replaceable>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Board size allowed for games (default 19).
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term><option>-verbose</option></term>
<listitem>
<para>
Print the GTP stream to the Go program to standard error.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<option>-version</option>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Print version and exit.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>

<para>
